text: Kitsap County is a county in the U.S. state of Washington. The county seat is Port Orchard. At the 2020 census, 275,611 people lived there. The county was founded on January 16, 1857. == References == Category:1857 establishments in the United States Category:1850s establishments in Washington (state) Category:Washington (state) counties
title: Kitsap County, Washington
